Home Assistant Add-on: TellStick with Telldus Live
====================================================

This software incorporates code and depends on libraries from multiple
open source projects. This file provides attribution and licensing
information for all components.

## Original Authors and Copyright Holders

### This Add-on
Copyright (C) 2019-2024 Erik Hilton <erikhilton73@gmail.com>
Copyright (C) 2024-2025 R00S (roosfork modifications)
Licensed under: GNU General Public License v3.0 or later

This add-on is a fork of erik73/addon-tellsticklive, which itself was
based on the now-deprecated official Home Assistant TellStick add-on.

Source: https://github.com/R00S/addon-tellsticklive-roosfork
Original: https://github.com/erik73/addon-tellsticklive

### Upstream Projects

#### Telldus Core (telldus-core)
Copyright (C) Telldus Technologies AB
Licensed under: GNU Lesser General Public License v2.1
Source: https://github.com/erik73/telldus (fork maintained by Erik Hilton)
Original: https://github.com/telldus/telldus

telldus-core provides the core daemon for TellStick hardware communication.
This add-on compiles and includes telldus-core and tdtool during the
Docker build process.

#### tellive-py
Copyright (C) Erik Johansson <erik@ejohansson.se>
Licensed under: GNU General Public License v3.0 or later
Source: https://github.com/erijo/tellive-py

tellive-py is a Python wrapper for Telldus Live cloud service, enabling
TellStick devices to connect to Telldus Live without requiring Telldus Center.
This add-on installs and uses tellive-py for cloud connectivity features.

#### tellcore-py
Copyright (C) Erik Johansson <erik@ejohansson.se>
Licensed under: GNU General Public License v3.0 or later
Source: https://github.com/erijo/tellcore-py

tellcore-py provides Python bindings for the TellStick Core library,
allowing Python programs to control TellStick devices. This add-on
installs and uses tellcore-py via pip.

#### Home Assistant Official Add-ons (deprecated tellstick)
Copyright (C) Home Assistant Team
Licensed under: Apache License 2.0
Source: https://github.com/home-assistant/addons

The original Home Assistant TellStick add-on was deprecated in December 2024.
This add-on continues to provide TellStick support based on the concepts
and integration patterns from the original implementation.

## License Compatibility

This combined work is licensed under the GNU General Public License v3.0
or later because it incorporates GPL v3 licensed components (tellive-py
and tellcore-py). The GPL v3 license is compatible with:

- LGPL 2.1 (telldus-core) ✓
- GPL v3+ (tellive-py, tellcore-py) ✓
- Apache 2.0 (concepts from Home Assistant addons) ✓ (one-way compatible)

## Third-Party Dependencies

This add-on also depends on the following packages installed via apk
and pip during the Docker build:

### Alpine Linux Packages
- confuse - Configuration file parser
- libftdi1 - Library for FTDI USB devices
- socat - Multipurpose relay for bidirectional data transfer

### Python Packages
- tellcore-py (as noted above)
- tellive-py (as noted above)

For specific version information, see the Dockerfile.

